# audiotap-helper bundle: committed as a prebuilt, ad-hoc-signed arm64 .app (like the other prebuilt
# helper binaries in bin/) so npm-installed users get it without a build. TCC needs a .app launched
# via LaunchServices, so this is a bundle rather than a bare binary. ensureHelperApp() rebuilds it from
# the committed Swift source on mtime change (developers only; shipped packages omit src). The
# entitlements file is a local build input and isn't needed at runtime.
bin/.audiotap.entitlements
xctest-runner/build/
